canonical:
  title: 旅寓
  author: 鄭夢周
  language: lzh
  text: 平生南與北心事轉蹉𧿶故國海西岸孤舟天一涯梅牎春色早板屋雨聲多獨坐消長日那堪苦憶家
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 旅寓
  author: 鄭夢周
  language: lzh
  text: 平生南與北。心事轉蹉𧿶。故國海西岸。孤舟天一涯。梅牎春色早。板屋雨聲多。獨坐消長日。那堪苦憶家。
korean:
  title: 여우
  author: 정몽주
  language: kor
  text: |-
    평생을 남쪽 또 북쪽으로
    마음과 일이 점점 틀려지네
    고국은 바다 서녘 편이요
    외로운 배는 하늘 한 가이어라
    매화 피어난 창엔 봄빛이 일찍 오고
    판자집에는 빗소리가 많다
    혼자 앉아 긴 날을 보내노니
    집 생각하는 괴로움 어이 견딜까
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0130_010_0350&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Sojourning Away
  author: Jeong Mong-ju
  language: eng
  text: |-
    A lifetime wandering south and north—
    my heart and circumstances grow ever at odds.
    My homeland lies beyond the western sea,
    and my lonely boat floats at heaven's edge.

    Early spring light finds the plum-blossom window,
    while rain-sounds crowd the wooden roof.
    Sitting alone, I pass the lengthening days,
    yet how can I endure this bitter ache for home?
  footnotes:
    - The 'western sea' likely refers to the poet's separation from Korea, viewing his homeland across the sea to the west.
    - The plum blossom is a traditional symbol of resilience and inner beauty in East Asian poetry, often representing the poet's noble character amid hardship.
